CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1774933457
OL,3,CShop price inflation edges up as
OL,4,C'storm clouds loom' ` BRC
OL,6,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,7,Fsaid: "Higher costs resulting from the
OL,8,Fconflict in the Middle East are
OL,9,Fstarting to feed into supply chains.
OL,11,F"While retailers will work with their
OL,12,Fsuppliers to mitigate the impact on
OL,13,Fprices as far as possible, inflation
OL,14,Fwill rise, although there are no
OL,15,Findications it will reach the peaks of
OL,16,Fthe last spike in April 2023.
OL,26,@oD@GOUsD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1774933457
OL,3,CShop price inflation edges up as
OL,4,C'storm clouds loom' ` BRC
OL,6,F"Government needs to look at all the
OL,7,Fcosts that could exacerbate these
OL,8,Fprice rises, from new healthy food
OL,9,Frules to trade changes with Europe,
OL,10,Fthe Employment Rights Act and non-
OL,11,Fcommodity charges which make up such a
OL,12,Flarge proportion of energy bills.
OL,13,FIgnoring businesses' concerns risks
OL,14,Feven higher prices for shoppers."
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/5
